short_description: Patrick Mackay was arrested in 1975 after killing Father Anthony Crean. He had butchered the priest with an axe and left him in a bath of blood. The killer's confessions would leave the police in a state of shock.

short_description: From Kharkiv to Bakhmut to Kherson, filmmaker Bernard-Henri Lévy documents the ravages of the war in the Ukraine through testimonies from soldiers and civilians.
